&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Rimes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rimes provides enterprise data management solutions to the global investment community. Driven by our passion for solving the most complex data problems, we provide our clients with investment intelligence that powers more than US$75 trillion in assets under management annually. The world’s leading institutional investors, asset managers and service providers rely on Rimes to help them make better investment decisions using accurate information and industry-leading technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Foundational Data team acts as the gatekeeper for all third-party communications with Rimes’s 800 information providers on behalf of our 400 end clients. The team manages key relationships with a huge and varied international group of information providers. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Acquisition Analyst’s role is vital to the Rimes infrastructure. Reporting to the Senior Manager of Foundational Data Acquisition, the Data Acquisition Analyst is responsible for working closely with external data partners to support new data acquisition, while keeping Rimes users informed of progress on any escalated issues. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is technically oriented, detail-focused, and persistent in seeing issues through to resolution. They should be able to manage multiple projects simultaneously, validate work proactively, and apply creative thinking to develop simple, effective solutions. Strong written and verbal communication skills are also essential, particularly when engaging with external data partners. In addition, the candidate should demonstrate a solid understanding of index data and experience in data analysis using basic to intermediate Excel functionalities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working with Python, SQL, and/or AI tools are advantageous to the role.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is open to fresh graduates or with 0-2 years work experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect with external data partners to support new data acquisition projects&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the maintenance and growth of the Rimes index catalogue, adding new records, and maintaining database integrity &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively maintain and keep up-to-date documentation of processes and procedures and communicate changes to the wider team &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify areas of improvement in existing processes and collaborate with team members to achieve greater efficiency and scalability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the suite of Rimes Foundational Data covering Benchmark &amp;amp; Indices, ETF, ESG, and Alternative data&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, analyse and resolve metadata gaps, creating new data content and mapping records across databases &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in finance, Business, or related study&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, interpersonal and organizational skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with, querying, and manipulating large datasets&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical thinking skills to interpret data, identify patterns, and support informed decision-making&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate MS Excel Skills (Match, Index, Lookup formulas, Pivot Tables)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities under tight deadlines&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work within a team as well as independently &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to learn modern technology and grow in an ever-changing environment&amp;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Rimes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rimes provides enterprise data management solutions to the global investment community. Driven by our passion for solving the most complex data problems, we provide our clients with investment intelligence that powers more than US$75 trillion in assets under management annually. The world’s leading institutional investors, asset managers and service providers rely on Rimes to help them make better investment decisions using accurate information and industry-leading technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Team at Rimes delivers cloud-based financial datasets that support critical investment decisions for institutional clients globally.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Data Developer, you will design and operate data pipelines on modern cloud platforms, transforming raw vendor data into validated, production-ready datasets. You will contribute to the scalability, reliability, and accuracy of the Rimes data platform, supporting both standardised and client-specific solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain scalable data pipelines using Databricks and PySpark to ingest, transform, and deliver financial datasets &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure datasets are accurate, consistent, and validated, supporting downstream analytics and reporting &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate and manage data from global vendors, adapting to feed changes and evolving data requirements &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business and client requirements into robust, production-ready data workflows &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product and client teams to deliver data outputs aligned to agreed timelines and quality standards &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to solutions supporting multiple asset classes and investment workflows &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate within structured processes and tooling to ensure traceability, control, and operational resilience of data pipelines&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong programming skills in Python and PySpark &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience working with Databricks or similar distributed data processing platforms &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with version control systems (e.g. Git) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in a technical discipline (e.g. Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 1 year of experience working with data in a technical or project-based context &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with structured or semi-structured data, with an emphasis on data transformation and validation &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills with a high level of accuracy and attention to detail &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to manage multiple tasks and priorities effectively &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear and effective communication skills &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working independently while collaborating across distributed teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SQL and data lake / lakehouse architectures &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data formats such as Parquet, XML, and ingestion via APIs &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to platforms such as Snowflake or Foundry (Palantir) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of financial markets or financial datasets &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Excel for data analysis or validation &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Progress toward CF

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Rimes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rimes provides enterprise data management solutions to the global investment community. Driven by our passion for solving the most complex data problems, we provide our clients with investment intelligence that powers more than US$75 trillion in assets under management annually. The world’s leading institutional investors, asset managers and service providers rely on Rimes to help them make better investment decisions using accurate information and industry-leading technology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Data Modeling Engineer, you will work hands‑on with financial datasets to make sure they are understood, structured correctly, and ready for downstream use. Alongside building data models, you will perform practical, early‑stage analysis on new datasets, checking fields, formats, and structure to ensure consistency and proper handling before the data enters our pipelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help ensure that new datasets, including index, pricing, reference, and research data, integrate smoothly into Rimes’ data ecosystem with clarity, quality, and traceability. This role is well suited for someone who enjoys rolling up their sleeves, exploring datasets directly, and shaping the underlying structures that power data workflows across the organization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect new datasets to understand their structure, fields, data types, and quirks before they are ingested. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify inconsistencies, missing fields, formatting issues, or schema gaps and flag what needs adjustment. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and update data models (tables, relationships, hierarchies) based on real dataset behavior. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test sample data against your models to ensure mappings, assumptions, and transformations are correct. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Data Engineering to translate your models into ETL/ELT‑ready schemas. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document field definitions, data relationships, and handling rules clearly for internal teams. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review provider schema updates and adjust models when needed to maintain alignment. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support data quality improvements by applying model‑level fixes and ensuring consistent patterns. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to straightforward improvements to modeling standards, documentation, and internal processes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
